            <title>[KAFKA-12928] Add a check whether the Task&apos;s statestore is actually a directory</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-12928</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I found this problem while working on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-10585&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;KAFKA-10585&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As of present,&#160;StateDirectory&#160;checks whether the Task&apos;s statestore directory exists and, if not, creates it. Since it does not check whether it is actually a directory, for example, if a regular file occupies the Task&apos;s statestore&apos;s path, the validation logic may be detoured.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
